405 template <typename T>
406 class WeakCallbackInfo {
407  public:
408  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
409 
410  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
411  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
412  Callback* callback)
413  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
414  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
415  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
416  }
417  }
418 
419  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
420  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
421  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
422 
423  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
424  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
425  return internal_fields_[0];
426  }
427  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
428  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
429  return internal_fields_[1];
430  }
431 
432  bool IsFirstPass() const { return callback_ != nullptr; }
433 
434  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
435  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
436  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
437  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
438  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
439  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
440  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
441 
442  private:
443  Isolate* isolate_;
444  T* parameter_;
445  Callback* callback_;
446  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
447 };

948  return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(slot));
949  }
950 
951  private:
952  internal::Object** Escape(internal::Object** escape_value);
953

955  // disallowing certain operations.

957  void operator=(const EscapableHandleScope&);
958  void* operator new(size_t size);
959  void operator delete(void*, size_t);

1152

1154  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is

1161  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.

1163  int length;
1164  bool rejected;
1165  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1166 
1167  private:

1171  };

5155 struct JitCodeEvent {
5156  enum EventType {
5157  CODE_ADDED,
5158  CODE_MOVED,
5159  CODE_REMOVED,
5160  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
5161  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
5162  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
5163  };
5164  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
5165  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
5166  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
5167  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
5168  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
5169  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
5170 
5171  // Type of event.
5172  EventType type;
5173  // Start of the instructions.
5174  void* code_start;
5175  // Size of the instructions.
5176  size_t code_len;
5177  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
5178  Local<UnboundScript> script;
5179  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
5180  // code line information which is returned from the
5181  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
5182  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
5183  void* user_data;

6436 template <class T>
6437 class Maybe {
6438  public:
6439  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6440  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6441 
6442  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6443  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6444  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6445  return value;
6446  }
6447 
6448  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6449  return has_value ? value : default_value;
6450  }
6451 
6452  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6453  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6454  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6455  }
6456 
6457  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6458  return !operator==(other);
6459  }
6460 
6461  private:
6462  Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6463  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6464 
6465  bool has_value;
6466  T value;
6467 
6468  template <class U>
6469  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6470  template <class U>
6471  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6472 };

6477  return Maybe<T>();
6478 }

6480 
6481 template <class T>
6482 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6483  return Maybe<T>(t);

6974 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6975 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6976 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6977 
6978 // Tag information for HeapObject.
6979 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6980 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6981 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6982 
6983 // Tag information for Smi.
6984 const int kSmiTag = 0;
6985 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6986 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6987 
6988 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6989 
6990 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6991 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6992  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6993  uintptr_t tagged_value =
6994  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6995  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6996 }
6997 
6998 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6999 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7000  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7001  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7002  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7003  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7004  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7005  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7006  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7007  }
7008  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7009  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7010  }
7011  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7012  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7013  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7014  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7015  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7016  //
7017  // CAUTION: The original code below:
7018  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7019  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7020  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7021  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7022  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7023  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7024  }
7025 };
7026 
7027 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7028 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7029  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7030  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7031  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7032  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7033  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7034  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7035  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7036  }
7037  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7038  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7039  }
7040  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7041  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7042  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7043  }
7044 };

7046 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
7047 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
7048 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
7049 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7050 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

7209  V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {

7217  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7218  return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);

7722 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
7723 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7724  typedef internal::Object O;
7725  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7726  typedef internal::Internals I;
7727  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7728  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7729  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7730  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
7731  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7732  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
7733  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
7734  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7735  }
7736 #endif
7737  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
7738 }
7739 
7740 
7741 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
7742 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7743  typedef internal::Object O;
7744  typedef internal::Internals I;
7745  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7746  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7747  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7748  if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
7749  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7750  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
7751  }
7752 #endif
7753  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
7754 }

8282 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8283  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8284  typedef internal::Internals I;
8285  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8286  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8287  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8288  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8289  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8290  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8291  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8292  int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8293  if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8294  amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8295  I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8296  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8297  }
8298  *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8299  return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8300 }
